net.hudup.core.alg

Class RecommendParam

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.hudup.core.alg.RecommendParam
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, TextParsable

    public class RecommendParam
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, Cloneable, TextParsable
    When a recommendation task is performed, a parameter of recommendation needs to be provided as an indicator. As a convention, this class is called recommendation parameter. For example, such parameter is input parameter of two main methods estimate(...) and recommend(...) of Recommender class to do actual tasks relevant to recommendation. Concretely, method estimate(...) estimates rating values based on such recommendation parameter. Method recommend(...) provides a list of items which are recommended to user based on recommendation parameter. Recommendation parameter contains important information as follows:
    • Initial rating vector which can be user rating vector or item rating vector, referred by internal variable ratingVector.
    • A profile which can be user profile containing user information (ID, name, etc.) or item profile containing item information (ID, name, price, etc.), referred by internal variable profile.
    • A context list relevant to how and where user (s) rates (rate) on item (s), referred by internal variable contextList.
    • Additional information, referred by internal variable extra, which must be serializable.
    Version:
    10.0
    Author:
    Loc Nguyen
